مِضْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDirFA","text_ar":"مَضِرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDirFA","text_ar":"خَضِرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took it without price:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in its fresh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"juicy, state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mDrA","text_ar":"مضرا"},{"kind":"text","text":"being an imitative sequent. (TA.) Whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDirapN","text_ar":"مَضِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~unoyaA xaDirapN","text_ar":"الدُّنْيَا خَضِرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the S"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulowapN xaDirapN","text_ar":"حُلْوَةٌ خَضِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The goods of this world are delicate, fresh, and pleasant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algazowu HulowN xaDirN","text_ar":"الغَزْوُ حُلْوٌ خَضِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Predatory warfare is sweet and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refreshing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and loved;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the victory and spoil attending it. (TA, from a trad. of Ibn- 'Omar [which see fully quoted voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vumaAmN","text_ar":"ثُمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"].) ―         -b2-  You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwalaka xiDorFA miDorFA","text_ar":"هُوَلَكَ خِضْرًا مِضْرًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is thine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for thee: may it be attended with enjoyment and a wholesome result."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba damahu xiDorFA","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ دَمَهُ خِضْرًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miDorFA","text_ar":"مِضْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDirFA","text_ar":"مَضِرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDirFA","text_ar":"خَضِرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His blood went unrevenged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unretaliated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unexpiated by a mulet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mDrA","text_ar":"مضرا"},{"kind":"text","text":"being an imitative sequent [here as in the former instance]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n10872","headword_ar":"خَضَرٌ","root":"xDr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDira","text_ar":"خَضِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [see 9, first sentence: ―         -b2-  and last sentence but one; and] see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorapN","text_ar":"خُضْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Green palm-branches with the leaves upon them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green palm-branches stripped of their leaves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaArN","text_ar":"اَخْضَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AHn.)"}],"source_refs":["Fr","K"]},{"entry_id":"n10873","headword_ar":"خَضِرٌ","root":"xDr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also A place"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having much verdure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxoDuwrN","text_ar":"يَخْضُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxoDarapN","text_ar":"مَخْضَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN xaDirapN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ خَضِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxoDuwrN","text_ar":"يَخْضُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land in which is much verdure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArD maxoDarapN","text_ar":"ارض مَخْضَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the Kur xxii. 62, accord. to one reading,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verdant land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiDorN","text_ar":"خِضْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places. ―         -b4-  Also, [as a subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is green:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, S, and Bd in vi. 99:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seed-produce;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Bd, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuD~aAraY","text_ar":"خُضَّارَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) so the former in the Kur ubi suprà: (Lth, Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly green herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a branch:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any branch."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaDiru","text_ar":"الخَضِرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The plant called"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albaqolapu AlxaDoraA='u","text_ar":"البَقْلَةُ الخَضْرَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaDirapu","text_ar":"الخَضِرَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaDiyru","text_ar":"الخَضِيرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxuDorapu","text_ar":"الخُضْرَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a green and rough herb"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plant, the leaves and fruit of which are like those of millet; it rises to the height of a cubit; and fills the mouth of the camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of plant of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobap","text_ar":"جَنْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) which latter term is applied to herbage whereof the root is deep in the earth, like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSiY~","text_ar":"نَصِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sil~iyaAn","text_ar":"صِلِّيَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [a coll. gen. n.:] n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not of the slender and succulent herbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plants, which dry up in summer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=kilapu AlxaDiri","text_ar":"ا=كِلَةُ الخَضِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., [properly signifying A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that eats the plant above mentioned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] applied to a man who acts justly and moderately with respect to worldly enjoyments: for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xDr","text_ar":"خضر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not of the slender and succulent herbs, as above observed, nor of those excellent plants which the spring produces by its consecutive rains, and which therefore become goodly and soft or tender; but of those upon which beasts pasture after others have dried up, because they find no others, and which the Arabs call"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobap","text_ar":"جَنْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the beasts do not eat much of it, nor do they find it wholesome. (IAth, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Lth","Bd","A","K","TA"]}]}}